            <h2 >About Cisco</h2>
            <p>
                Cisco Systems, Inc. is a leading multinational technology conglomerate that specializes in networking hardware, software, telecommunications equipment, and cybersecurity solutions. Headquartered in San Jose, California, USA, Cisco has played a pivotal role in the growth of the internet and digital communication since its inception in 1984. The company was founded by Leonard Bosack and Sandy Lerner, two computer scientists at Stanford University, who developed early network protocols to connect different computer systems. 
            </p>
            <p>
            Ciscoâ€™s core business revolves around designing and selling networking solutions, including routers, switches, and wireless systems, which form the backbone of modern communication networks. Over the years, Cisco has diversified its portfolio to include cloud computing, Internet of Things (IoT) solutions, artificial intelligence (AI)-driven technologies, and cybersecurity products. Its flagship networking operating system, Cisco IOS, is widely recognized in the industry.
            </p>
            <p>
                As of 2024, Chuck Robbins serves as the Chairman and CEO of Cisco, a position he has held since 2015. Robbins has been instrumental in shifting Cisco's focus toward software and subscription-based services, moving away from its traditional reliance on hardware sales.

                Cisco operates globally, with a presence in over 100 countries and more than 80,000 employees. Its customers range from small businesses to large enterprises, including government agencies, educational institutions, and healthcare organizations. Cisco's innovative solutions empower organizations to enhance connectivity, improve efficiency, and secure digital assets. 
            </p>

            <p>
                The company is known for its emphasis on acquisitions as part of its growth strategy. Cisco has acquired several companies to expand its technological capabilities, such as AppDynamics, Meraki, and Duo Security. These acquisitions have strengthened its offerings in cloud-based solutions, network security, and data analytics.

                Cisco is also a leader in promoting sustainability and corporate social responsibility (CSR). Through initiatives like Cisco Networking Academy, the company has trained millions of students and professionals worldwide in IT and networking skills, fostering talent development in the technology sector.

                Listed on the NASDAQ stock exchange under the ticker symbol CSCO, Cisco is a Fortune 500 company and one of the most valuable brands in the tech industry. Its commitment to innovation, customer-centric solutions, and a secure digital future has solidified its position as a market leader in the rapidly evolving tech landscape.
